			<div class="article-correspondence layout-item fill-pattern-light">
		<div class="layout-item-intro">
			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="588">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>Lee Martin&rsquo;s essay &ldquo;<a href="/article/4629">No Ears Have Heard</a>&rdquo; [February 2012] shows that true compassion can come only after we suspend our judgments and try to understand each other. He quotes his former teacher, poet Miller Williams: &ldquo;You do not know what wars are going on / down there where the spirit meets the bone.&rdquo;</p>

<p>Here in the penitentiary, vitriolic language, impulsive reactions, and violent behaviors are commonplace, a manifestation of the prisoners&rsquo; existential despair. I strive to keep in mind that most felons are undereducated and come from homes where they were subjected to neglect and abuse and had poor role models.</p>

<p>Suspending my self-righteous disgust and disapproval, I can often recognize the painful void where their &ldquo;spirit meets the bone.&rdquo;</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">R.B.<br>Sumner, Illinois</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

								<div class="block-correspondence" id="518">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>My brother unexpectedly passed away from liver failure on Valentine&rsquo;s Day this year. He was only thirty-five. After his death, my husband and I were reading the February issue of <em>The Sun</em> in bed. I&rsquo;d had an appointment with my counselor earlier in the day, and she&rsquo;d advised me to reach out to my friends, but I wasn&rsquo;t sure how. Then I read &ldquo;<a href="/article/4629">No Ears Have Heard</a>,&rdquo; by Lee Martin.</p>

<p>In the last column of the essay, he writes, &ldquo;In that instant she invited me into her grief.&rdquo; I knew then that I somehow had to invite my friends into my own grief.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Carmel Montgomery<br>Portland, Oregon</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

					</div>

